WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
as the same, commit thou to faithful men

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:05.960
who shall be able to teach others also.

00:00:05.960 --> 00:00:08.659
And I'm thankful for faithful men.

00:00:08.659 --> 00:00:11.899
I'm thankful for my dad, of course, Father's Day.

00:00:11.899 --> 00:00:13.539
Sent him a message early this morning.

00:00:13.539 --> 00:00:17.079
I'm thankful that when I was just almost a teenager,

00:00:17.079 --> 00:00:19.639
12 years old, almost 13,

00:00:19.639 --> 00:00:22.280
that my dad trusted Christ as his savior.

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:25.440
Somebody cared enough about him to share the gospel.

00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:28.280
Wasn't even really sharing the gospel with him directly,

00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:30.520
but with another co-workers who's in the Marine Corps

00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:33.000
and overheard that conversation.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:34.580
And just a couple of weeks after that,

00:00:34.580 --> 00:00:36.740
he trusted Christ as his savior.

00:00:36.740 --> 00:00:39.759
And I'll tell you, my life changed after that

00:00:39.759 --> 00:00:41.520
because dad said, we're going to church.

00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:44.240
And I began to go to church and hear the gospel.

00:00:44.240 --> 00:00:46.200
It was a number of years before I got saved,

00:00:46.200 --> 00:00:48.080
but I'm thankful to be able to report

00:00:48.080 --> 00:00:50.919
that my dad's still serving the Lord today.

00:00:50.919 --> 00:00:53.680
And that is a blessing and an encouragement to me

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:56.759
and thankful for the faithful men of our church.

00:00:56.799 --> 00:00:59.759
And often I pray that God would give us men,

00:00:59.759 --> 00:01:02.439
that God would give us faithful men,

00:01:02.439 --> 00:01:04.720
those that would serve the Lord faithfully,

00:01:04.720 --> 00:01:07.599
that we could run the race and serve the Lord.

00:01:07.599 --> 00:01:10.580
Thankful for the examples of those that have gone before us.

00:01:10.580 --> 00:01:12.080
If you have your Bible with you this morning,

00:01:12.080 --> 00:01:14.480
Isaiah chapter 38 is where we'll be looking at.

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:16.720
Isaiah chapter number 38.

00:01:16.720 --> 00:01:19.559
And of course, it is a great responsibility.

00:01:19.559 --> 00:01:20.559
It's a great blessing,

00:01:20.559 --> 00:01:22.900
but also a great responsibility to be a father.

00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:25.720
And I remember with great clarity

00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:27.760
when Holly made known to me

00:01:27.760 --> 00:01:30.800
that she was expecting our first child.

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:33.919
And I remember that, and I would say it this way,

00:01:33.919 --> 00:01:37.480
that there was a flood of emotions that overwhelmed me.

00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:41.160
And some of those that I could specifically say,

00:01:41.160 --> 00:01:44.400
joy, excitement, but I'll be honest with you,

00:01:44.400 --> 00:01:45.559
there was a little bit of fear

00:01:45.559 --> 00:01:47.319
and a little bit of uncertainty

00:01:47.319 --> 00:01:49.800
and the weight of the responsibility

00:01:49.800 --> 00:01:52.080
of being a father and having children.

00:01:52.080 --> 00:01:54.720
And I remember Holly sharing that with me.

00:01:54.720 --> 00:01:58.480
Now our kids are 23 and 21 and 19, all adults,

00:01:58.480 --> 00:02:02.040
but just a blessing to be able to have the privilege

00:02:02.040 --> 00:02:04.419
and the responsibility to have children.

00:02:04.419 --> 00:02:06.480
We know that children are an heritage of the Lord

00:02:06.480 --> 00:02:08.119
and it's a blessing.

00:02:08.119 --> 00:02:09.600
And we're very thankful.

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:14.600
One of the greatest responsibilities as a Christian father

00:02:14.759 --> 00:02:17.479
is noted in a phrase here in the book of Isaiah

00:02:17.479 --> 00:02:18.699
in the 38th chapter.

00:02:18.699 --> 00:02:20.479
I want you to look at verse 19.

00:02:20.479 --> 00:02:22.679
I'm gonna quickly go through the entire chapter

00:02:22.679 --> 00:02:23.660
by way of introduction,

00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:26.880
but I'm gonna just read verse 19 to begin here.

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:27.720
And the Bible says this,

00:02:27.720 --> 00:02:30.460
the living, the living, he shall praise thee

00:02:30.460 --> 00:02:31.520
as I do this day.

00:02:31.520 --> 00:02:34.360
Notice the last phrase of verse 19,

00:02:34.360 --> 00:02:39.360
the father to the children shall make known thy truth.

00:02:41.259 --> 00:02:44.539
What a powerful declaration, a powerful statement.

00:02:44.539 --> 00:02:46.440
And as Christian fathers,

00:02:46.440 --> 00:02:49.639
we understand the great responsibility

00:02:49.639 --> 00:02:52.899
that is given to us here in this verse of scripture.

00:02:52.899 --> 00:02:54.679
No doubt as fathers,

00:02:54.679 --> 00:02:56.279
there are many valuable lessons

00:02:56.279 --> 00:02:58.059
that we can teach our children.

00:02:58.059 --> 00:03:02.419
And I've had the, again, opportunity to have three children

00:03:02.419 --> 00:03:04.460
and we're very thankful for that.

00:03:04.460 --> 00:03:07.139
Many lessons that you try to teach your children,

00:03:07.139 --> 00:03:08.919
you teach them to have good manners

00:03:08.919 --> 00:03:10.820
and you teach them to behave a certain way

00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:14.059
and you teach them various things about finances and life

00:03:14.059 --> 00:03:15.100
and so on and so forth.

00:03:15.100 --> 00:03:17.179
But honestly, this morning,

00:03:17.179 --> 00:03:20.919
at the top of our list as Christian fathers

00:03:20.919 --> 00:03:23.580
should be to teach them about God,

00:03:23.580 --> 00:03:27.720
to teach them about God and to make known thy truth.

00:03:27.720 --> 00:03:29.119
Here in Isaiah chapter 38,

00:03:29.119 --> 00:03:31.360
there's an interaction that takes place

00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:36.199
between King Hezekiah and the prophet Isaiah.

00:03:36.199 --> 00:03:38.800
Now, Hezekiah was basically a good king.

00:03:38.800 --> 00:03:41.199
There are many good things that you can read about Hezekiah

00:03:41.199 --> 00:03:43.339
and as you look at this particular chapter,

00:03:43.339 --> 00:03:45.160
we find that the Bible says in verse number one,

00:03:45.160 --> 00:03:49.759
in those days was Hezekiah sick unto death.

00:03:49.759 --> 00:03:51.639
And Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amos,

00:03:51.639 --> 00:03:54.860
said unto him and said unto, sorry, let me back up.

00:03:54.860 --> 00:03:57.000
And Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amos,

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:01.479
came unto him and said unto him, notice where he says,

00:04:01.479 --> 00:04:06.440
thus saith the Lord, set thine house in order

00:04:06.440 --> 00:04:10.139
for thou shalt die and not live.

00:04:10.139 --> 00:04:11.660
And we understand through the interaction

00:04:11.660 --> 00:04:13.479
that takes place here that Hezekiah

00:04:13.479 --> 00:04:16.880
would be granted 15 years of additional life.

00:04:16.880 --> 00:04:18.359
But let me say it this way,

00:04:18.359 --> 00:04:20.440
it did come to the point one day

00:04:20.440 --> 00:04:22.839
in Hezekiah's life that he died.

00:04:22.839 --> 00:04:25.200
The Bible says as it appointed unto man wants to die

00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:26.880
and after this, the judgment,

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:28.519
I don't know when I'm gonna die,

00:04:28.519 --> 00:04:30.279
you don't know when you're going to die,

00:04:30.279 --> 00:04:33.519
but we understand the truth of God's word

00:04:33.519 --> 00:04:34.720
with regard to this.

00:04:34.720 --> 00:04:37.279
But think about this interaction

00:04:37.279 --> 00:04:39.359
as the prophet of God, Isaiah,

00:04:39.359 --> 00:04:42.559
comes and says to the king, Hezekiah,

00:04:42.559 --> 00:04:46.040
thus saith the Lord, here's the message from God,

00:04:46.040 --> 00:04:47.679
you're gonna die.

00:04:47.679 --> 00:04:50.760
Notice he says, set thine house in order

00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:54.920
for thou shalt die and not live.

00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.040
And we find that the Bible tells us

00:04:57.040 --> 00:04:59.859
that Hezekiah turned his face toward the wall

00:04:59.859 --> 00:05:01.679
and prayed unto the Lord and said,

00:05:01.679 --> 00:05:04.359
remember now, O Lord, I beseech thee

00:05:04.359 --> 00:05:06.320
how I have walked before thee in truth

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:07.880
and with a perfect heart,

00:05:07.880 --> 00:05:09.839
and have done that which is good in thy sight.

00:05:09.839 --> 00:05:12.200
And Hezekiah wept sore.

00:05:12.200 --> 00:05:14.239
Then came the word of the Lord to Isaiah saying,

00:05:14.239 --> 00:05:16.959
go and say to Hezekiah, thus saith the Lord,

00:05:16.959 --> 00:05:20.220
the God of David, thy father, I have heard thy prayer,

00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:22.160
I have seen thy tears.

00:05:22.160 --> 00:05:27.160
Notice, behold, I will add unto thy days 15 years,

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:29.399
and I will deliver thee in this city

00:05:29.399 --> 00:05:31.200
out of the hand of the king of Assyria,

00:05:31.200 --> 00:05:34.000
and I will defend this city.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.399
And this shall be a sign unto thee from the Lord

00:05:36.399 --> 00:05:39.940
that the Lord will do this thing that he had spoken.

00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:42.359
Behold, I will bring again the shadow of the degrees,

00:05:42.359 --> 00:05:45.559
which has gone down in the sundial of Ahaz,

00:05:45.559 --> 00:05:47.519
10 degrees backward.

00:05:47.519 --> 00:05:50.440
So the sun returned 10 degrees

00:05:50.440 --> 00:05:53.760
by which degrees it was gone down.

00:05:53.760 --> 00:05:56.519
In verse number nine, the Bible says this,

00:05:56.519 --> 00:05:59.160
the writing of Hezekiah, king of Judah,

00:05:59.160 --> 00:06:03.079
when he had been sick and was recovered of his sickness.

00:06:03.079 --> 00:06:04.720
And so starting in verse number nine,

00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:07.359
down really through verse number 20,

00:06:07.359 --> 00:06:11.160
we find that Hezekiah begins to reference some things,

00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:14.279
to write some things, to acknowledge some things

00:06:14.279 --> 00:06:16.160
that he knew to be true.

00:06:16.160 --> 00:06:17.399
And he talks about praising,

00:06:17.399 --> 00:06:18.799
and he talks about various things,

00:06:18.799 --> 00:06:19.839
but I want you to notice,

00:06:19.839 --> 00:06:22.359
and for sake of what we're looking at this morning,

00:06:22.359 --> 00:06:24.720
I want you to notice near the end of this writing,

00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:27.559
near the end of this declaration,

00:06:27.559 --> 00:06:29.880
in verse number 19, he says,

00:06:29.880 --> 00:06:33.920
the living, the living, he shall praise thee

00:06:33.920 --> 00:06:36.600
as I do this day.

00:06:36.600 --> 00:06:39.519
And then notice, these are the words of Hezekiah,

00:06:39.519 --> 00:06:44.519
the father to the children shall make known thy truth.

00:06:44.799 --> 00:06:48.320
He knew something that was extremely important.

00:06:48.320 --> 00:06:51.079
Unfortunately, in Hezekiah's life,

00:06:51.079 --> 00:06:53.720
the son that would be born after

00:06:53.720 --> 00:06:56.119
this particular circumstance was a man

00:06:56.119 --> 00:06:57.760
by the name of Manasseh.

00:06:57.760 --> 00:06:59.739
Manasseh was 12 when he began to reign,

00:06:59.739 --> 00:07:01.320
and he was a wicked man.

00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:02.880
And it doesn't necessarily say that,

00:07:02.880 --> 00:07:05.679
that doesn't mean that Hezekiah didn't teach him.

00:07:05.679 --> 00:07:07.320
We don't know all of the details,

00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:10.600
but what I'd say is that Hezekiah recognized

00:07:10.600 --> 00:07:13.920
an extremely important truth that's necessary

00:07:13.920 --> 00:07:16.640
for each of us to understand this morning,

00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:21.640
that somebody, someone needs to make God's truth known

00:07:21.859 --> 00:07:23.559
to the next generation.

00:07:23.559 --> 00:07:25.720
And as we look at the context,

00:07:25.720 --> 00:07:28.160
and we think about this day being Father's Day,

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:29.839
that here it specifically says,

00:07:29.839 --> 00:07:34.320
the father to the children shall make known thy truth.

00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:36.760
Can I tell you this morning by way of introduction,

00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:40.160
that it's every believer's responsibility

00:07:40.160 --> 00:07:42.940
to make known the truth of God's word.

00:07:42.940 --> 00:07:44.920
We just recently had our missions conference,

00:07:44.920 --> 00:07:47.600
and obviously preaching and being challenged

00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:49.600
about the idea of going forth

00:07:49.600 --> 00:07:52.959
and preaching the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:07:52.959 --> 00:07:55.839
We understand the fullness of the Great Commission

00:07:55.839 --> 00:07:58.600
is not simply to preach the gospel.

00:07:58.600 --> 00:08:00.399
The fullness of the Great Commission

00:08:00.399 --> 00:08:02.100
is to preach the gospel.

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:03.399
The Bible says that we're to go

00:08:03.399 --> 00:08:05.359
and we're to preach the gospel to every creature,

00:08:05.359 --> 00:08:07.839
but we find that we're to baptize them,

00:08:07.839 --> 00:08:08.920
and then notice this,

00:08:08.920 --> 00:08:13.920
to teach them all things whatsoever I have commanded thee.

00:08:14.079 --> 00:08:16.399
The idea of discipleship,

00:08:16.399 --> 00:08:20.559
the idea that we're to go forth and make disciples.

00:08:20.559 --> 00:08:24.179
And so this morning, the truth that is before us

00:08:24.179 --> 00:08:26.959
this morning is for every single one of us.

00:08:26.959 --> 00:08:31.019
We have a responsibility to make God's truth known

00:08:31.019 --> 00:08:34.359
to those that are coming behind us.

00:08:34.359 --> 00:08:36.760
We understand there's a time to live,

00:08:36.760 --> 00:08:38.280
there's a time to die.

00:08:38.280 --> 00:08:41.679
We understand that there's one generation that passes away,

00:08:41.679 --> 00:08:43.559
and there's another generation that comes.

00:08:43.559 --> 00:08:45.440
We can look through the Bible,

00:08:45.440 --> 00:08:48.080
we can look specifically in the Old Testament

00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:49.520
and understand many things

00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:51.599
with regard to the nation of Israel,

00:08:51.599 --> 00:08:54.140
and we can see a nation that's living and serving

00:08:54.140 --> 00:08:55.799
and has good leadership,

00:08:55.799 --> 00:08:58.159
and then another generation rises up,

00:08:58.159 --> 00:09:00.820
and there's always another generation.

00:09:00.820 --> 00:09:01.880
We look in the New Testament,

00:09:01.880 --> 00:09:03.559
begin to think about the leaders,

00:09:03.559 --> 00:09:05.679
the spiritual leaders of the church

00:09:05.679 --> 00:09:10.080
and how the Lord had instructed them to teach

00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:13.359
and to disciple a future generation.

00:09:13.359 --> 00:09:16.520
I'm thankful that Paul had the opportunity

00:09:16.520 --> 00:09:19.000
to pass the baton to Timothy.

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:21.280
I'm thankful that Paul had the opportunity

00:09:21.280 --> 00:09:24.320
to instruct Titus and to leave him in Crete

00:09:24.320 --> 00:09:26.359
that he would set in order the things

00:09:26.359 --> 00:09:28.000
that were wanting there.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:30.039
Begin to think about the ministry

00:09:30.039 --> 00:09:34.679
and the idea of making God's truth known

00:09:34.679 --> 00:09:36.619
to the next generation.

00:09:36.619 --> 00:09:38.200
From that verse of Scripture,

00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:40.280
I've simply titled the message this morning,

00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:42.479
Make Known Thy Truth.

00:09:42.479 --> 00:09:44.840
When we talk about thy truth, that's God's truth,

00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:46.039
not your truth.

00:09:46.039 --> 00:09:47.000
That's God's truth,

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:49.799
and we have to understand that we're making known

00:09:49.799 --> 00:09:51.580
the truth of God's word.

00:09:51.580 --> 00:09:54.200
I'm thankful this morning that Jesus said,

00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:57.239
I am the way, the truth, and the life.

00:09:57.239 --> 00:09:59.919
No man cometh unto the Father but by me.

00:09:59.919 --> 00:10:01.599
Thankful that Jesus said this,

00:10:01.599 --> 00:10:04.199
sanctify them through thy word.

00:10:04.199 --> 00:10:06.839
Thy word is truth.

00:10:06.839 --> 00:10:08.719
And just a little while after that,

00:10:08.719 --> 00:10:11.519
Pilate stood before Jesus and asked what is truth?

00:10:11.519 --> 00:10:15.119
And truth embodied stood right before him

00:10:15.119 --> 00:10:18.239
and yet he didn't stick around long enough to get an answer.

00:10:18.239 --> 00:10:19.639
I am thankful this morning

00:10:19.639 --> 00:10:21.999
that we have the truth of God's word.

00:10:21.999 --> 00:10:24.999
I'm thankful that we have a Bible that's dependable,

00:10:24.999 --> 00:10:25.999
that we can look to.

00:10:25.999 --> 00:10:28.719
It's all scriptures given by inspiration of God.

00:10:28.719 --> 00:10:32.839
It's been supernaturally preserved for us

00:10:32.839 --> 00:10:35.439
and we're so thankful that we have a Bible,

00:10:35.439 --> 00:10:37.599
that we have the truth before us.

00:10:37.599 --> 00:10:38.759
So we're gonna think about this idea

00:10:38.759 --> 00:10:39.979
of make known thy truth.

00:10:39.979 --> 00:10:41.519
Just a few thoughts for you

00:10:41.519 --> 00:10:43.719
and we'll be looking at various parts

00:10:43.719 --> 00:10:44.759
of the Bible this morning.

00:10:44.759 --> 00:10:46.399
But number one, if you're taking notes,

00:10:46.399 --> 00:10:49.399
a plea for influence.

00:10:49.399 --> 00:10:51.399
A plea for influence.

00:10:51.399 --> 00:10:53.439
Look over at the 71st Psalm, if you will.

00:10:53.439 --> 00:10:54.879
Psalm 71.

00:10:54.879 --> 00:10:56.239
We're gonna look at a few verses here

00:10:56.239 --> 00:10:57.759
in the book of Psalms this morning

00:10:57.759 --> 00:11:00.879
and we'll eventually get into the New Testament.

00:11:00.879 --> 00:11:03.859
But I want you to see here in this Psalm,

00:11:03.859 --> 00:11:06.639
a plea for influence.

00:11:06.639 --> 00:11:08.159
And we begin to understand,

00:11:08.159 --> 00:11:09.079
there are some that say,

00:11:09.079 --> 00:11:11.079
well, I just don't have any influence.

00:11:11.079 --> 00:11:13.359
There's some that say, I wish I had influence.

00:11:13.359 --> 00:11:16.959
But here we see the heart of the Psalmist

00:11:16.959 --> 00:11:19.959
having this plea, this earnest desire,

00:11:19.959 --> 00:11:22.719
this yearning to have influence.

00:11:22.719 --> 00:11:25.439
The Bible says in Psalm 71 in verse number 18,

00:11:25.439 --> 00:11:26.359
notice the Bible says,

00:11:26.359 --> 00:11:29.759
now also, when I am old and gray-headed,

00:11:29.759 --> 00:11:32.359
oh God, forsake me not,

00:11:32.359 --> 00:11:34.079
notice the rest of the verse,

00:11:34.079 --> 00:11:38.639
until I have showed thy strength

00:11:38.639 --> 00:11:40.559
unto this generation

00:11:40.559 --> 00:11:44.439
and thy power to everyone that is to come.

00:11:44.439 --> 00:11:46.799
Do you see the heart of the Psalmist here

00:11:46.799 --> 00:11:48.559
in Psalm 71 in verse 18,

00:11:48.559 --> 00:11:50.479
this plea for influence.

00:11:50.479 --> 00:11:52.279
He recognized his condition.

00:11:52.279 --> 00:11:54.879
He recognized that he was old and gray-headed

00:11:54.879 --> 00:11:56.999
and he recognized that there was still

00:11:56.999 --> 00:11:58.759
within him this drive,

00:11:58.759 --> 00:12:01.199
this desire to be able to influence.

00:12:01.199 --> 00:12:02.359
He makes this plea.

00:12:02.359 --> 00:12:05.799
He says, oh God, forsake me not

00:12:05.799 --> 00:12:07.159
until I have showed.

00:12:07.159 --> 00:12:08.359
Now that's an interesting word.

00:12:08.359 --> 00:12:10.019
That word means to tell.

